          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " people erroneously call street racing. Taking part in those kinds of activities not only puts you at risk, you’re endangering innocent people on the road. However, if you do go street racing, don’t then make an insurance claim when you inevitably crash. That’s exactly what Michael Lynn Cooper, 55, of Ontario, California is accused of doing and the man’s now facing multiple felony counts of insurance fraud and grand theft.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
